For the crayfish stock, put the garlic, spring onions, prawn heads and shells, white wine, tomato pur√©e, ketchup and water into a medium saucepan; place on the heat and boil for eight minutes. Strain over a bowl, reserving the stock and discarding the shells and vegetables.For the pasta sauce, pour the strained stock back into the pan, add the cream and spring onion and cook over a medium heat for two minutes. Stir in the tomato.To serve, put the spaghetti into two pasta bowls and top with the sauce.